.gitignore (file)                                             - to ignore formats containing in this gitignore file

________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Git Commands

git --version                                                 - to know version of git

git config --global user.name                                 - to create git account (username)
git config --global user.email                                - to create git account (email)
git config --list                                             - to check information of git account

git help <command>                                            - to get help of git commands
git help add                                                  - to get help of add command
git help commit                                               - to get help of commit command

git clone <gitacc-url>                                        - to download git repository

git init                                                      - initialize an existing directory as a Git repository
git status                                                    - to get update of git account

git log                                                       - show all commits in the current branchâ€™s history

git add <file>                                                - to add file to staging area
git commit -m <"something">                                   - to save your changes to local repository
git push                                                      - to push commit changes to remote server(local repository)

git difftool HEAD                                             - to view difference between current and previous codes ( HEAD is the last commit)
git difftool <HEAD~1> <HEAD~2>                                - to view difference between (HEAD-1 commit and HEAD-2 commit) previous two commits
git difftool -t <tool-name>                                   - to open this tool respect to difftool

git checkout -- <file>                                        - to undo changes your code(1 file) of repository of local computer
git checkout .                                                - to undo changes your codes(all the files) of repository of local computer
git revert <commit-ID>                                        - to undo commit changes of your code
git reset --hard <commit-ID>                                  - to undo all the changes after this commit ID

git branch                                                    - to print all the branches of your repository
git branch <branch-name>                                      - to create new branch
git checkout <branch-name>                                    - to active this branch (switched to this branch)
git push --set-upstream origin <branch-name>                  - to add branch to your cloud github account

git merge <branch-name> <active-branch>                       - to merge this branch into active branch
git mergetool                                                 - to make marging

git pull                                                      - get updated contents of github from internet









